	doi = {10.1093/mnras/stv1786},
	abstract = {We calibrate here cosmological radiative transfer simulations with
ATON/RAMSES with a range of measurements of the Ly α opacity from
Quasi-Stellar Objects (QSO) absorption spectra. We find the Ly α
opacity to be very sensitive to the exact timing of hydrogen
reionization. Models reproducing the measured evolution of the mean
photoionization rate and average mean free path reach overlap at z
˜ 7 and predict an accelerated evolution of the Ly α opacity
at z {\textgreater} 6 consistent with the rapidly evolving luminosity function of
