10-4 Zsolar, contain one clump with 99\% of the mass, while the two with metallicities Z=10-3 and
10-2 Zsolar each contain two clumps that share most of the mass. The Z=10-3 Zsolar simulation also produced two low-mass protostellar objects with masses between 10-2 and 10-1 Msolar. Gas with
Z{\textgreater}=10-3 Zsolar is able to cool to the
temperature of the cosmic microwave background (CMB), which sets a lower limit to the minimum fragmentation mass. This suggests that the
second-generation stars produced a spectrum of lower mass stars but were still more massive, on average, than stars formed in the local universe.},
