relationship in which regions of equal molecular gas surface density can
form stars at quite different rates. These data have been interpreted as
implying either that different star formation laws may apply in
different circumstances, that the star formation law is sensitive to
large-scale galaxy properties rather than local properties, or that
there are high-density thresholds for star formation. Here we collate
